1. Nf3 Nf6 ({Our favourite Reti first move, and now we'll tackle everything apart from} 1... d5 {which was, of course, the subject of the Modern Reti: Part One [/variation/23789295].}) ({A very common, flexible and important alternative to} 1... d5 {.}) 2. c4 {Our ideal second move, one just as good against 1...Nf6 as 1...d5. Now Nc3 and/or e2-e3 will follow.} c5 {Black heads for the theoretically important waters of the Symmetrical English. There are, however, some major and pretty common alternatives.} 3. Nc3 {Natural development. White will usually follow up with e2-e3 then d2-d4, although we'll push the pawn instead to e4 if Black now goes in for a fianchetto on the kingside.} Nc6 {Maintaining the symmetry is a very important option, but so are Black's two principle alternatives.} 4. e3 {White gets ready to break with d2-d4 and we'll come on to this sub-variation of the Symmetrical in Chapter 2c [/variation/35967462/#/4/w].} e5 $5 5. d4 {Breaking in the centre before Black can get in ...e4.} cxd4 6. exd4 e4 ({White is quite happy to acquire easy development after} 6... exd4 7. Nxd4 {, when Be2 and O-O may quickly follow or even a disruptive check with Qe2+.}) 7. Ne5 $1 {As Black isn't really in a position to exchange on e5, White heads forwards and will now look to quickly complete kingside development with Be2 and O-O.} Bb4 8. Be2 Qa5 9. Nxc6 {The simplest way of dealing with the pressure against e5 and c3. Black can't now both recapture the piece and take twice on c3 due to Bd2.} dxc6 10. Bd2 O-O 11. O-O {White has decent central control, is set to challenge on the queenside with a2-a3 and in the short term Black's bridgehead on e4 shouldn't be too troublesome.} Re8 12. a3 Bxc3 13. bxc3 $5 {An unexpected recapture, but one which keeps the black queen away from g5. Ahead of gradually putting the bishop-pair to good use, White would now like to restrict Black's possibilities with the important prophylactic move h2-h3, as well as go maybe a3-a4, Qc2 and Be3, as we'll see further in Chapter 2c2 [/variation/35967514/#/13/w].} *

