1. Nf3 c5 ({Our favourite Reti first move, and now we'll tackle everything apart from} 1... d5 {which was, of course, the subject of the Modern Reti: Part One [/variation/23789295].}) {Black offers a Sicilian...} 2. c4 ({Nf3 Nf6} 2. c4 {c5 Nc3}) {g6 e4 As is our preference, where possible, against an early ...g6 and ...c5 combination, we get ready to break with d2-d4 and set up the Maroczy Bind after ...cxd4 Nxd4. Bg7 d4 cxd4 Now} 2... Qa5 {can be simply met by} 3. Nc3 {and 4...Qb6 also isn't too disruptive in view of 5.dxc5! Qxc5 6.Be2 with a pleasant edge. Nxd4 Qb6!? Here play will tend to transpose to the mainline of the Symmetrical English/Accelerated Dragon ( Chapter 2b [/variation/35967414/#/7/w]) after} Nc6 {Be3 Nf6 , although Black does have the odd alternative 6...Nh6 , after which 7.h3 keeps them out of g4. Nb3 The knight needed to retreat, but this position still feels like a definite edge for White, with the Maroczy Bind and Be3 then Qd2 on the way, as we'll see further in Chapter Three [/variation/35967567/#/7/w].} *

