{A creative way of preventing d2-d4. e3 White wastes no time in dealing with the intruder on d4. Nxf3+ Qxf3 g6 d4!? -- A critical advance. Clearly cxd4 exd4 only helps White's central control. Now White should be happy to swipe the pawn on c5 if allowed, even at the cost of doubled or even trebled (if Black flicks in ... Bg7xc3+) pawns.} 1. Nf3 c5 ({Our favourite Reti first move, and now we'll tackle everything apart from} 1... d5 {which was, of course, the subject of the Modern Reti: Part One [/variation/23789295].}) {Black offers a Sicilian...} 2. c4 ({...But we decline the chance for} 2. e4 {and instead make our favourite second move, the same as we do against 1...d5. We're now officially in the realm of the Symmetrical English and} Nf6 3. Nc3 {would take play into the world of Chapter Two [/variation/35967305/#/3/w] ( 1.Nf3 Nf6 2.c4 c5 3.Nc3 ).}) 2... Nc6 3. Nc3 ({Nf3 Nf6 c4 c5} 3. Nc3 {Nc6}) *

