1. Nf3 e6 ({Our favourite Reti first move, and now we'll tackle everything apart from} 1... d5 {which was, of course, the subject of the Modern Reti: Part One [/variation/23789295].}) 2. c4 {of the repertoire, while} b6 3. e3 {and} {here [/variation/35967817/#/3/b]} f5 {e3 are dealt with in Chapter of this part. Instead,} {here [/variation/35967802/#/3/w]} 4. c5 {Nc3} Nf6 {( 3...d5 4.cxd5 exd5 5.d4 is a Tarrasch Queen's Gambit - again see Part One [/variation/23789957/#/5/w]) 4.e3 is a move order discussed at the start of Chapter Two [/variation/35967305/#/3/w/1.12]. Play is then likely to either remain in Symmetrical English waters, head back into a Tarrasch Defence or towards the Queen's Indian-type lines we also cover in this second part of the repertoire, ones which can also arise here via the other important move order 2...Nf6 3.e3 .} *

