1. Nf3 b5 ({Our favourite Reti first move, and now we'll tackle everything apart from} 1... d5 {which was, of course, the subject of the Modern Reti: Part One [/variation/23789295].}) {The Polish Defence is possible with White having not opened 1.e4, but our move order does allow us to quickly target b5.} 2. e3 a6 3. a4 $1 {Undermining and weakening the black queenside without delay.} b4 4. d4 Bb7 5. Bd3 {As we'll see further in Chapter 8a [/variation/35967867/#/5/w], White enjoys a promising version of a Colle. O-O then a central advance with Nbd2 and e3-e4 will follow, while on the queenside White should find both c2-c3 and a4-a5 rather useful moves to bear in mind.} *

