htly awkward pawn weaknesses, so he should likely prefer one of the other two recaptures, of which 12...Qxd5 feels a little risky and might be met by 13.Ba3!? .}) 13. dxc5 {Bringing our favourite fianchettoed bishop into play.} Bxc5 14. Rc4 $1 {An aggressive rook lift and also one which seizes the initiative. White threatens to force a major weakness with Rg4, while also preparing to increase the pressure after Qa1 and maybe Rfd1 (or Qb1 and Bd3 if Black goes in for an ...f6 defence).} *

