1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e3 Nxc3 {This forcing approach is often the choice of a Grünfeld player, but, worry not, we don't have to transpose into their favourite opening.} 6. bxc3 ({The more dynamic and more popular recapture, although if you're happy to grind away in a queenless middlegame,} 6. dxc3 Qxd1+ 7. Kxd1 {is by no means a bad choice, as used by Andersson, Miles and even Carlsen. With the text move, White holds back on d2-d4, waiting to see what Black is up to and now 6...Bg4?! would be well met by 7.Qb3 , pressing against b7 and f7.}) 6... Nc6 7. d4 {It's high time to make use of the extra central pawn which the exchanges on d5 and c3 have given us. White now threatens d4-d5 and Black doesn't have an especially good sort of Semi-Tarrasch.} cxd4 8. exd4 $1 {A strong and dynamic recapture, keeping the idea of d4-d5 high on the agenda. White would now like to quickly complete development through Bd3 and O-O, with Rb1 also likely to be quite a useful move.} e6 9. Bd3 Be7 10. O-O {Kingside development is complete and it's not hard to appreciate that White would quite like to exploit the absence of a knight on f6 to attack if Black follows suit. Qc2 will tickle h7, Re1 or Rb1 will prepare a timely rook lift and there may even be ideas of h2-h4, intending Ng5 or Bxh7+ and being happy to sacrifice the pawn to exchange another of Black's defensive pieces while opening lines, such as for Re3-h3.} b6 11. Re1 ({With} 11. Bb5 {fairly well met by} Bd7 {, White is content to improve his forces while teeing up a certain pawn advance.}) 11... Bb7 12. h4 $1 Bxh4 $2 ({A strong advance. Black has so far managed to delay castling, and now} 12... O-O {will be fairly well met by} 13. Ng5 {. That is also a strong response to both 12...Qd7 and 12...Qc7, which all means that White is doing pretty well and, yes, the h-pawn is pretty much taboo.}) 13. Nxh4 Qxh4 14. d5 $1 {The classic breakthrough in such a structure and one here which the engines feel should be met by Black giving up a piece.} Nd8 $2 15. Re4 $1 {The initiative is already a deadly one, with Qa4+ and Ba3 on their way.} *

