open. Pushing e3-e4 may be a good approach (not least in the event of} 11... Nd7 12. e4 {when e4-e5 may follow), the bishop can also use e4 and there are ideas too of both Ba3 and Qc2, angling to get in h4-h5 after all.}) 12. Be4 $1 {With a threat as White demonstrates that the pin on the knight is not to be feared.} Nc6 13. Ba3 {A fine post for the bishop, threatening to take on c5. White should be slightly for choice with Qb3 or even Qa4 on the way.} *

