sing to let the bishop settle as White is determined to proceed with the h5-h6 and Ne4 plan.} Bd7 12. h6 Bf8 $5 ({Now Black must either retreat of allow one or} 12... Bf6 13. Ne4 {and 12...Be5 13.d4 (or even 13.f4 ).}) 13. Ne4 Z0 ({Played with a threat, but the knight will be quite good on c5 and may even go there in the event of} 13... c4 $5 {, i.e. with} 14. Nc5 {. Meanwhile both c3-c4 and d2-d4 are also on the agenda and White should be slightly for choice in this rather unusual position.}) *

