fle when the bishop can make it out via e5.} Rg8 12. Be5 $1 Nxe5 ({Heading for g3. A key point is, of course, that} 12... Rxg2 $2 13. Bg3 {would entomb the black rook.}) 13. Nxe5 {White threatens not only Bxh7, but Qh5 to take full advantage of Black's broken-up kingside.} Rg5 $2 14. f4 $1 {With tempo as White remains determined to activate the queen to the maximum.} Rxg2 15. Qh5 {Hitting f7 as White realises that there's no need to fear the check on h4.} Bh4+ 16. Kd1 $1 {White was a a pawn down, but also clearly for choice in Cordova-Chandra, Las Vegas 2021. Not only is mate threatened on f7, but there are potential tactics involving Nxf7 and White should also be looking for ways to involve the rooks, such as with a timely Rc7 or, if the g2-rook retreats, Ke2 and Rhg1.} *

