for now.}) 12... Be7 13. Qh5+ $1 Kf8 ({An aforementioned check. Now} 13... Bf7 14. Qh3 {would be a bit awkward for Black on the light squares.}) 14. f4 $5 {White simply castled in Bernasek-Votava, Czech League 2019, but with Black not up to much, there's no need to rush with that and more ambitious plans may also be available.} Qd7 15. h3 $5 {The position is scarcely completely clear, but White clearly has decent compensation with Black's kingside pieces far from completely happy. Here Kf2 will connect the rooks and White would like to expand with g2-g4, ideally followed by Rhg1 and a fairly powerful breakthrough in the shape of g4-g5.} *

