1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e3 Nc6 6. Bb5 $1 ({Natural development from Black and a fairly popular move at all levels. Now} 6. d4 e6 {would take play into an important line of the Semi-Tarrasch.}) {White continues to develop rapidly and this is a very useful pin, already intending to increase the pressure with Ne5 or Qa4 if allowed.} 6... Nc7 $6 7. Bxc6+ {White is quite happy to be provoked and the black knight not especially happy on c7.} bxc6 8. Qa4 {This is why White was happy to be provoked as c6 can quickly be targeted (likewise, 6...a6?! would be well met by 7.Bxc6+ bxc6 8.Qa4 ).} Qd6 9. O-O {Once again housing the king before ...Ba6 becomes an issue and now Rd1 may follow and/or b2-b3 and Ba3.} Ba6 $5 10. Rd1 {White may now even be ready to seize a strong early initiative with d2-d4, as well as just to go b2-b3 and Ba3.} Bb5 11. Qa5 {Renewing the idea of d2-d4 or just b2-b3 and Ba3 when Bxc5 might even be on, overloading the black queen.} Bd3 12. Ne1 $1 {Forcing the pace as White threatens to win a piece.} Bg6 13. d4 $5 ({There's also nothing wrong with} 13. b3 {and Ba3 if you prefer, but}) (13. d4 {is simply a strong advance, threatening dxc5 and, of course, 13...cxd4? 14.Rxd4 would not spell good news for Black down the d-file.}) *

