1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e3 Nc6 6. Bb5 $1 ({Natural development from Black and a fairly popular move at all levels. Now} 6. d4 e6 {would take play into an important line of the Semi-Tarrasch.}) {White continues to develop rapidly and this is a very useful pin, already intending to increase the pressure with Ne5 or Qa4 if allowed.} 6... Nxc3 {Black's most popular choice in practice, altering the structure.} 7. bxc3 {The dynamic recapture, keeping ideas of Ne5 and Bxc6+ high on the agenda, while also intending to seize an early initiative with O-O then d2-d4. White has scored very well from here in practice, with Black usually now attempting to avoid being saddled with doubled c-pawns.} Bd7 8. O-O {Housing the king as there's no need to rush with d2-d4 here, with White also happy to provoke ... a6.} e6 {Black's most common and solid defence.} 9. d4 Be7 ({There's nothing better here than this useful central advance. Now if} 9... a6 {the bishop can simply regroup with} 10. Bd3 {. Meanwhile White may expand with e3-e4 or perhaps prefer to probe, beginning with Rb1.}) 10. Rb1 $5 {)} (10. e4 {has been more popular and can scarcely be a bad move, of course, but here we're happy to maintain control and begin to probe, with b7 and h7 targets after any subsequent Bd3.}) 10... a6 11. Bd3 b5 ({Played with a certain threat and White might now meet} 11... Qc7 {with} 12. Bd2 {, keeping Black out of b4 and thereby intending e3-e4 when Qe2 and e4-e5 might even follow.}) 12. a4 bxa4 ({Thematically undermining the advanced black queenside at the first opportunity, in part because} 12... c4 $6 13. Be4 {would now but increase the pressure on Black, as would 12...b4?! 13.dxc5 .}) {This was seen in Prusikin-Schreiner, Austrian League 2017, where White could have played to regain the pawn.} 13. Bc2 $1 {Perhaps Black isn't doing too badly, but White will now regain the pawn and can always follow up Bxa4 with Qd3 and Bc2, which may well threaten mate on h7 and so force a weakness. White's strong centre also looks to be a more useful asset in the short to medium term than the passed pawn on a6.} *

