1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e3 Nc6 6. Bb5 $1 ({Natural development from Black and a fairly popular move at all levels. Now} 6. d4 e6 {would take play into an important line of the Semi-Tarrasch.}) {White continues to develop rapidly and this is a very useful pin, already intending to increase the pressure with Ne5 or Qa4 if allowed.} 6... Nxc3 {Black's most popular choice in practice, altering the structure.} 7. bxc3 {The dynamic recapture, keeping ideas of Ne5 and Bxc6+ high on the agenda, while also intending to seize an early initiative with O-O then d2-d4. White has scored very well from here in practice, with Black usually now attempting to avoid being saddled with doubled c-pawns.} Bd7 8. O-O {Housing the king as there's no need to rush with d2-d4 here, with White also happy to provoke ... a6.} e6 {Black's most common and solid defence.} 9. d4 Be7 ({There's nothing better here than this useful central advance. Now if} 9... a6 {the bishop can simply regroup with} 10. Bd3 {. Meanwhile White may expand with e3-e4 or perhaps prefer to probe, beginning with Rb1.}) 10. Rb1 $5 (10. e4 {has been more popular and can scarcely be a bad move, of course, but here we're happy to maintain control and begin to probe, with b7 and h7 targets after any subsequent Bd3.}) 10... O-O 11. Bd3 {Unfurling an attack on b7, while hoping that White will be able to get something going on the kingside at some point.} Qc7 {Covering b7. This is also how Jeffery Xiong has met both 11.Qe2 and 11.Re1 in this line.} 12. Qe2 {Calmly does it as White prepares to maintain control and slowly edge forwards with Bd2 followed by e3-e4, with a quick h2-h4 another possible aggressive advance.} cxd4 $6 13. exd4 $1 {Once again, this is an exchange which White should welcome, since Re1 may follow and then Ng5 and/or h2-h4, all the while as Black rather lacks counterplay.} Rac8 14. Re1 Na5 $6 15. Ne5 {Exploiting the black knight's absence from c6. White ties the black queen down to the defence of the bishop on d7 and is all set to increase the pressure with d4-d5, Bf4 or even an attack on h7.} *

