 $5 18. cxd6 {A logical follow-up, one which leaves Black suffering whether or not he now gambits a pawn.} exd6 19. Rd4 $1 {Overprotecting e4 while preparing to double on the d-file with Qd2, while now ...b4 can be met by Nd1, after which Ne3 will leave White in control and clearly better.} *

