 when they wonder about}) (11. Ne2 $5 {.}) 11... Qa5 12. Qe2 $5 {) Calmly overprotecting the bishop on b5 as White offers a pawn for the initiative.} Nxd4 $6 13. Nxd4 Bxd4 14. Nxd5 {Seizing the initiative and threatening both Nxe7+ and Bc7.} Bxc5 $6 15. Rac1 Z0 ({The position is most precarious for Black (both} 15... Z0 16. Rxc5 {and 16.b4 Bxb4 17.g4 are threatened), and the engines confirm that White is doing pretty well.}) *

