1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nc3 Nc6 4. e3 e5 {An ambitious central advance, setting up a reversed Botvinnik central formation.} 5. d4 {Needless to say, we react in the centre, threatening dxe5 as well as d4-d5.} e4 $5 {The modern try and likely the critical line.} 6. d5 ({A forcing continuation, designed to retain a fair degree of control. The big alternative is} 6. Ne5 {, but by avoiding an exchange on d4, Black has given himself some extra options and would appear to be OK in an unclear scenario after} g6 {and even 6...h5!? .}) 6... exf3 {Without a good square for his knight, Black pretty much must exchange so.} 7. dxc6 {White threatens to win a pawn and here all three of Black's captures have seen a reasonable degree of testing.} dxc6 {The most solid continuation, offering an exchange of queens.} 8. Qxd8+ ({White must exchange so and force the king to move, not allow Black to seize the initiative with} 8. Qxf3 $2 Bg4 9. Qg3 Bd6 {.}) 8... Kxd8 9. gxf3 {White's structure is the more healthy one (our central pawns can advance with somewhat more purpose than Black's rather stymied queenside majority), and we would like to obtain some pressure down the long dark-square diagonal, ideally with b2-b3 and Bb2 in conjunction with Rg1.} Be6 10. b3 {A familiar plan, intending Bb2 and O-O-O+.} b6 (10... Kc7 11. Bb2 Be7 12. Bd3 {White wants to generate a bit of pressure against h7, as well as support an f3-f4-f5 advance. It's also, of course, possible to first castle, while the engines quite like 12.h4!?.} Rhd8 13. O-O-O b6 14. Ne2 $1 {Sending the knight towards f4 in conjunction with h2-h4, ideally followed by h4-h5 and perhaps even Be5+, left White with a definite pull in Guramishvili-Harika, Teheran (rapid) 2017.}) 11. Bb2 Ke7 12. Ne4 $1 ({This was tried in Aronian-Erigaisi, Goldmoney Asian Rapid 2021, where} 12. f4 g6 13. Bg2 Rc8 {seemed solid enough for Black, so White might prefer a different plan.}) 12... Nxe4 13. fxe4 {The pressure against g7 and imminent expansion with f2-f4 followed by f4-f5 or e4-e5 gives White a pleasant edge.} *

