s best, angling for a small plus.} Nxe5 10. Bxd7+ Nxd7 11. Nxe7 {Ensuring that White will emerge with a small minor piece advantage.} Qxe7 12. O-O O-O 13. b3 {This position has led to a couple of unexciting draws, but doesn't have to, unless White is feeling unambitious. Black is very solid, but White threatens to pin with Ba3. He is also all set to go Bb2 and can recapture on d4 with the queen, after which it should be possible to probe on either flank, not least against a7 and down the open central files.} *

