exchange. He will now follow up with O-O and Re1, and Black may regret having exchanged off one of the defenders of his kingside in the king's knight.} Be7 10. O-O O-O 11. Re1 {Phase one of development is complete. The queen's rook may now take up a decent role on b1, and White should be looking for a timely Bd3, swinging the bishop back to support the potential attack on the black king.} Bf6 12. Rb1 Bd7 13. Bd3 {This dropped back with tempo against b7 in Feuerstack-Mihajlov, Vienna 2015. White may now continue with Ne5 or even h2-h4, gambiting a pawn in conjunction with the striking idea of Rb5-h5.} *

