1. Nf3 c5 2. c4 {We decline the option of a Sicilian (2.e4), and keep play within Reti-English lines, getting ready to go 3.Nc3 or 3.e3.} g6 {Black's third main option at this point, after which play is likely to transpose to the Accelerated Dragon lines we saw in Chapter 2b [/variation/35967401/#/3/b].} 3. e4 $1 ({A perhaps unexpected advance, but, worry not, the plan is not a Botvinnik formation, but rather a Maroczy Bind after all, as White plans to follow through with d2-d4 then Nc3. With this approach we avoid being move ordered by} 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nc6 {, as well as the possibility of}) (3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 d5 $5 {. After 3...Nc6 play might immediately transpose into the realm of 2b [/variation/35967401/#/6/w] after 4.d4 cxd4 5.Nxd4 .}) 3... Bg7 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nc6 ({Establishing the Maroczy Bind. 6.Nc3 will follow, and} 5... Nf6 6. Nc3 {would be an immediate transposition back into 2b [/variation/35967401/#/6/w].}) 6. Be3 Nh6 ({Defending the knight and now play will almost always go} 6... Nf6 7. Nc3 {(and not 7.e5? Qa5+ ) or 6...d6 7.Nc3 Nf6 8.Be2 when we're back in the world of 2b [/variation/35967446/#/8/b]. There are just two minor alternatives we should mention where Black aims to exploit the absence of an early ...Nf6.}) 7. h3 $5 {Once again, we find this to be a rare but appealing prophylactic move, keeping the knight out of g4 and thereby threatening Qd2.} d6 $6 8. Qd2 {Now Black must either lose time and make a miserable retreat to g8 or go in for multiple exchanges.} Nxd4 9. Bxd4 Bxd4 10. Qxd4 O-O 11. Nc3 {After a few forced recaptures, this is a very natural move. White enjoys a pleasant advantage already and may simply continue with Be2 and O-O, although with that knight misplaced on h6 you may well prefer something more aggressive and more potent, involving queenside castling and a pawn storm.} Be6 12. O-O-O $5 f6 13. f4 $1 {White's king is pretty safe, unlike its counterpart and with g2-g4 next up, a promising attack was brewing in Egelstaff-C.White, correspondence 2019.} *

