is somewhat less messy than} 12. Qh5+ Kd8 {. White now has ideas of c4-c5, as well as Be2 and O-O.}) 12... d6 13. Be2 {White enjoys at least a very pleasant edge. The simple plan is O-O, f2-f4 and then, if Black has wisely avoided castling into an attack on the kingside, Bh5+ and Bf3, with Rab1 and Rb5 another useful idea to bear in mind.} *

