he queen just yet and now Bd3 will follow.} d6 12. Bd3 Qa5 13. O-O {The pawn on e4 had gone, but White still enjoyed another pleasant edge in Roiz-Shukh, Russian Team Championship 2010. Re1 is likely to follow, beginning to exert some pressure down the e-file and there are also ideas of both Be4 and Nd5, ideally in conjunction with a fairly powerful advance of the queenside pawns.} *

