1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. h4 $1 {Consistent with our approach in Chapter 2a1 [/variation/35967336/#/7/w] ( 2...c5 3.Nc3 d5 4.cxd5 Nxd5 5.e3 Nxc3 6.bxc3 g6 7.h4 ), and a very well-established choice these days at this point, with even Magnus having appeared on the white side. The idea is simple: to exert early kingside pressure with h4-h5. Instead, 5.d4 would just be a standard Grunfeld, but if you like to explore complex sidelines away from the beaten track, you may wish to look into 5.Qb3 Nb6 and only then 6.h4!? .} Bg7 {Black's most common response, retaining the tension, although a great many moves have actually been tried here - testament to the strength as well as one-time surprise factor of 5.h4.} 6. h5 ({Needless to say, we press ahead when allowed, introducing ideas of h5-h6 and e2-e4, as well as hxg6, although it should be noted that the calm} 6. e4 $5 Nxc3 7. dxc3 {is also quite a good option.}) 6... Nc6 $5 7. d4 $1 ({It's important to contest the centre and not fall too far behind in development here. Indeed,} 7. Qb3 $6 Be6 $1 8. Qxb7 $6 Ndb4 {would not be wise and Black also obtains good counterplay after 7.h6 Bf6 and then the slow 8.Ne4 (8.g3 is a much better approach) 8...Bf5 .}) ({Instead, with} 7. d4 {we threaten to dominate the centre and the board after e2-e4 and don't forget that Black has obstructed one major source of counterplay in ...c5.}) 7... Nb6 $5 8. e3 ({Calm does it, now that} 8. e4 $2 {would just drop d4.}) ({After} 8. e3 {White is all set to meet} Bg4 {with} 9. h6 Bf6 10. Be2 {followed by O-O.}) 8... O-O 9. hxg6 $5 ({The most direct, although} 9. Be2 {is also a good approach, simply intending h5-h6 and O-O, with a likely edge.}) 9... hxg6 10. Bd2 {A modest development, but White wants to go Qc2 and then O-O-O or even Qe4.} e5 11. Nxe5 $1 {Forcing exchanges while clearing the f-pawn for active service.} Nxe5 12. dxe5 Bxe5 ({White is now set to roll the e3- and f2-pawns forwards and might meet} 12... Qg5 $5 {with} 13. e4 {or 13.Ne2!? Qxe5 14.Bc3 .}) 13. f4 {With e3-e4 and Qf3 as well as O-O-O high on the agenda, White already enjoyed a strong initiative in Narayanan-Sismeiro, Ovar 2022.} *

