1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. h4 $1 {Consistent with our approach in Chapter 2a1 [/variation/35967336/#/7/w] ( 2...c5 3.Nc3 d5 4.cxd5 Nxd5 5.e3 Nxc3 6.bxc3 g6 7.h4 ), and a very well-established choice these days at this point, with even Magnus having appeared on the white side. The idea is simple: to exert early kingside pressure with h4-h5. Instead, 5.d4 would just be a standard Grunfeld, but if you like to explore complex sidelines away from the beaten track, you may wish to look into 5.Qb3 Nb6 and only then 6.h4!? .} Bg7 {Black's most common response, retaining the tension, although a great many moves have actually been tried here - testament to the strength as well as one-time surprise factor of 5.h4.} 6. h5 ({Needless to say, we press ahead when allowed, introducing ideas of h5-h6 and e2-e4, as well as hxg6, although it should be noted that the calm} 6. e4 $5 Nxc3 7. dxc3 {is also quite a good option.}) 6... e5 $5 {Rare, but hardly terrible.} 7. e4 ({Forcing the pace (} 7. d4 $5 {, intending} exd4 8. Bg5 {is another decent option), as White hopes for 7...Nf4? 8.d4! or 7...Nb4 8.d3 followed by a2-a3, which is also pretty good when Black isn't in a position to inflict any damage with ...Nc6-d4 and/or ...Bg4. Likewise, 7...Nxc3 8.bxc3 followed by Bc4 must be fairly pleasant for White.}) 7... Nb6 8. a4 $5 {Preparing to tickle Black's queenside and so forcing a small weakness on b5 unless Black wants to allow a4-a5.} a5 9. d4 $1 {A vigorous pawn sacrifice. White prepares to use the b5-square, and not for the bishop for once.} exd4 10. Nb5 {White threatens to regain the pawn with Nbxd4 and a definite pull, while also pressing on c7 and introducing the idea of Bg5 in conjunction with h5-h6.} Bg4 11. Bg5 $1 {Played anyhow, as one intermezzo can answer another. White will either now follow up with h5-h6 then Be2, or in the following way.} Bxf3 12. Qc1 $1 {White is temporarily a piece down, but does have three large threats.} f6 {This seems to be relatively the best defence.} 13. Bf4 Z0 ({Again, White has three threats in} 13... Z0 14. gxf3 {, 14.Nxc7+ and even 14.Bxc7 , and so will regain the material with decent interest.}) *

