 same drill: e2-e4 will follow with a huge early initiative, unless Black prefers to lose at once after} 11... Bf8 $2 12. d5 $1 Qxd5 13. Rd1 Qe6 14. Ng5 Qf6 15. Ne4 Qe6 16. Nd6+ $1 {. A fairly long line, but one ideally not so hard to visualise, as well as enjoy.}) 12. e4 Bd7 13. Bb5 {Here Black could find nothing better than to castle and give up a piece for far too little compensation in Navara-Djukic, European Team Championship, Terme Catez 2021. That wasn't quite forced, but the engines suggest it may well have been the best try.} e5 $2 14. dxc5 {With tempo while also opening up the d-file.} bxc5 15. Rd1 Qc7 16. Rxd7 $1 ({Even stronger than} 16. Bxc5 {. The attack's a killer.}) 16... Kxd7 17. O-O {Not only is Rd1+ a huge threat, but so is Qc4 in conjunction with Qxc5 or just Bxc5 and Rd1-d6.} *

