ck would obtain some compensation. Instead, White expands in the centre - and in powerful fashion.}) 12... Ne5 13. d6 $1 {Driving a wedge deep into the heart of the black position as White plays for control of d5. Strategically Black is already in some trouble and White may follow up with Be2 and O-O or a more aggressive O-O-O and h2-h4-h5 approach.} *

