anwhile, all of h4-h5, O-O-O and Bh6 are on their way.}) {Ugly, but how else to prevent h4-h5?} 13. O-O-O ({It's also quite possible to go} 13. Be2 {and O-O, but we're happy again to house the king on the queenside. The dark-squared bishop may go to h6 or just sit on g5, while Bd3 and f2-f3 will prepare a timely g2-g4 break. Factor in too the idea of Ne2-f4 and Black's position does not look an especially appealing one.}) *

