1. Nf3 d6 2. d4 $1 ({A fairly rare, but not unimportant move order, and one which both your authors have used on occasion. Black prepares ...e5, and so this is a rare position where we do not advocate} 2. c4 {.}) ({The best move order for the purpose of our repertoire, although you can also prefer} 2. c4 e5 3. d4 {if you don't mind playing against Black's space advantage after} e4 4. Ng5 {.}) ({The move} 2. d4 {simply intends c2-c4, Nc3 and e2-e4 and now play will usually transpose to either our mainline [/variation/35967728/#/3/w] here after} Nf6 3. c4 {or to the realm of 6b [/variation/35967761/#/4/w] after 2...g6 3.e4 Bg7 4.c4 . There are though two independent options.}) 2... f5 {This move orders us out of our proposed anti-Dutch lines in Chapter Seven, but a simple solution is at hand.} 3. Nc3 $1 {Obstructing the c-pawn it's true, but White wants to break quickly with e2-e4 to exploit a weakening downside to the early ...f5.} Nf6 4. Bg5 Nbd7 ({Continuing to play for control of e4. White has scored well from here.} 4... e6 5. e4 fxe4 6. Nxe4 {is a pleasant edge, 4...g6?! 5.Bxf6 exf6 6.d5! positionally grim for Black, and so too is 4...Ne4?! 5.Nxe4 fxe4 6.Nd2 .}) {Black's standard reply, maintaining piece control of f6 and so indirectly also e4.} 5. Qd3 $1 {) This has established itself as White's main move, attacking f5 and so forcing through e2-e4 after all.} g6 6. e4 {Continuing to force the pace. In view of the threats of exf5 and e4-e5, Black pretty much must exchange on e4.} fxe4 7. Nxe4 {All is now set for O-O-O, after which even Re1 may become an awkward idea for Black to face, with another strong possibility that of h2-h4-h5, sometimes in conjunction with Ng3.} Bg7 8. O-O-O c6 9. Re1 $1 O-O ({Forcing Black to either evacuate their king from the centre or accept coming under pressure after} 9... Nxe4 10. Qxe4 Nf6 11. Qh4 {.}) {Here White was happy to check on b3 in Banikas-Pezelj, Skopje 2018, and he could have done even better:} 10. Ng3 $1 {Keeping pieces on to accentuate Black's problems while simply intending to race Harry down the board with h2-h4-h5. Black is already in some difficulties.} *

