nd Qd2.} Ne7 8. Be3 ({White settled for} 8. Be2 {in Heinzel-Jansa, Bayerisch Eisenstein 2012, but might have been more ambitious.}) {White is now all set to castle long then begin to expand on the kingside where all of the pawns on f3, f2 and h2 would quite like to trundle down the board.} 8... Nf5 $2 {This would be good, but for...} 9. Qe4+ $1 Ne7 10. Qxb7 {White is a pawn up and with the superior development.} *

