dxe5 Ng8 11. Bf4 {would leave White in full control and clearly better.}) 10. Be3 $5 ({Preparing to fight for the initiative and quickly castle long, at the cost of a pawn. White preferred the sensible enough} 10. Bg2 {in Maksimenko-Srebrnic, Murska Sobota 2008, but please don't fall for}) (10. Bf4 $2 Nxd4 $1 11. Nxd4 dxe5 {.}) 10... dxe5 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. Nxe5 {Consenting to further exchanges ahead of finally fianchettoing the bishop, with tempo.} Bxe5 13. Bg2 c6 14. O-O-O Z0 ({With f2-f4 on the horizon (an advance} 14... Qc7 15. Ne2 {will force through), White has promising compensation. The knight may also be deployed to e4, while the rooks will be quite happy on d1 and e1 or doubled on the d-file, and, crucially, just where will the black king find safe sanctuary, if anywhere?}) *

