1. Nf3 g6 {The Modern Defence, although in practice this flexible move order from Black will often lead to the King's Indian.} 2. e4 $1 ({Like 1.Nf3 d6 2.d4 this is a perhaps unexpected choice, but it avoids being move ordered into something we don't want. Indeed,} 2. d4 Nf6 3. c4 Bg7 4. Nc3 d5 {would see Black having tricked us into a Grunfeld after all, while 2.c4 Bg7 3.Nc3 can be annoyingly met by 3...c5 . If your opponent isn't a Grunfeld or Symmetrical English player, you may not need to worry and so can allow those options, but the text move, intending d2-d4 and only then c2-c4 is the best route towards a King's Indian transposition or lines of the Modern not unacceptable to White. Note, too, that now 2...c5 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 followed by -- 5.c4 would take us back into the Maroczy Bind world of 2b [/variation/35967401/#/4/w].}) 2... Nf6 $6 {A premature involvement of the knight, if a surprise choice which you may get to face at blitz or rapid.} 3. e5 $1 {Taking up the challenge.} Nh5 {The North Sea Defence, a sometime favourite of the world number one's at blitz and bullet.} 4. d4 {Classical play as White helps himself to the control of the centre on offer.} d6 5. Bc4 $1 d5 ({White's best move, generating some pressure against f7 and so enabling us to meet} 5... Bg7 $6 {with} 6. Ng5 {, threatening both Nxf7 and g2-g4.}) 6. Bd3 {White has more often gone to e2, but this is also a good square for the bishop.} Bg4 7. h3 {Refusing to allow Black to settle.} Bxf3 8. Qxf3 {White's space advantage and potential light-square pressure are not insignificant and already both the c2-c4 and g2-g4 advances loom.} e6 9. g4 $5 {In Pyhala-Heinola, Jyvaskyla 1994 White calmly castled then broke with c2-c4, but it was also possible to force the pace.} Ng7 10. Bh6 $1 {Played before Black can get ...h5 in. Now untangling the kingside won't be at all easy unless Black goes in for a small tactic.} Nf5 $5 11. Bxf8 Nh4 12. Qg3 {Not exactly a bad square for the queen, keeping an eye on the errant knight.} Rxf8 13. Nd2 {With O-O-O and f2-f4 on the way, White is somewhat for choice.} *

