1. Nf3 g6 {The Modern Defence, although in practice this flexible move order from Black will often lead to the King's Indian.} 2. e4 $1 ({Like 1.Nf3 d6 2.d4 this is a perhaps unexpected choice, but it avoids being move ordered into something we don't want. Indeed,} 2. d4 Nf6 3. c4 Bg7 4. Nc3 d5 {would see Black having tricked us into a Grunfeld after all, while 2.c4 Bg7 3.Nc3 can be annoyingly met by 3...c5 . If your opponent isn't a Grunfeld or Symmetrical English player, you may not need to worry and so can allow those options, but the text move, intending d2-d4 and only then c2-c4 is the best route towards a King's Indian transposition or lines of the Modern not unacceptable to White. Note, too, that now 2...c5 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 followed by -- 5.c4 would take us back into the Maroczy Bind world of 2b [/variation/35967401/#/4/w].}) 2... Nf6 $6 {A premature involvement of the knight, if a surprise choice which you may get to face at blitz or rapid.} 3. e5 $1 {Taking up the challenge.} Nh5 {The North Sea Defence, a sometime favourite of the world number one's at blitz and bullet.} 4. d4 {Classical play as White helps himself to the control of the centre on offer.} d6 5. Bc4 $1 d5 ({White's best move, generating some pressure against f7 and so enabling us to meet} 5... Bg7 $6 {with} 6. Ng5 {, threatening both Nxf7 and g2-g4.}) 6. Bd3 {White has more often gone to e2, but this is also a good square for the bishop.} Ng7 $5 7. O-O {Calmly housing the king while waiting to see what Black will do with his light-squared bishop.} Bf5 8. c4 $1 c6 ({It's high time to obtain some pressure. Now} 8... dxc4 $6 9. Bxc4 e6 10. Nc3 {would be positionally a bit suspect for Black.}) 9. Nc3 {White is now ready to exchange on d5, f5 then go Qb3, forking b7 and d5.} Bxd3 10. Qxd3 e6 11. b3 $5 ({This gives White the option of ...dxc4; bxc4. One plan is now g2-g4 and h2-h3 to try and trap the knight on g7 (} 11. g4 $5 {is also possible), another Bg5 or just Bd2, after which White might even be set to proceed full steam ahead on the queenside with c4-c5, b3-b4, etc.}) *

