1. Nf3 f5 2. c4 Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. b3 {Heading for our favourite Reti set-up with the white dark-squared bishop on the long diagonal.} Be7 ({Black's standard move order in the normal Classical Dutch, i.e. 1.d4 f5 2.c4 Nf6, etc, but here they might also begin with} 4... d6 {, angling for a quick ...e5 at the cost of a tempo. White can cut out such ideas with} 5. d4 {when} Be7 6. Bb2 O-O 7. Nc3 {would take us back into the current trainable.}) 5. Bb2 O-O 6. Nc3 {White keeps the d-pawn flexible while getting ready for cxd5 and g2-g3 in the event of a Stonewall.} d6 {Angling to break out with ...e5.} 7. d4 {Slamming the brakes on Black's idea. We're now into a conventional Dutch, although it should be said that this is another pretty unusual move order and has rarely occurred via a 1.d4 f5 move order.} Qe8 {Black's most common choice according to ChessBase in the limited practice with this position so far, angling for an early kingside attack, just as Classical Dutch players often like to do.} 8. Qc2 $1 {This looks like the right way to support the key e4 break. White may even be able to follow up with Bd3, and if ...Nc6 then a2-a3.} ({Stuart Conquest, though, was once happy just to calmly go} 8. Be2 {followed by O-O, and}) (8. Bd3 {can hardly be terrible, even if here} Nc6 $5 9. d5 Ne5 {is more murky than usual due to Black's ideas of ...Nxd3+ and ...Qg6.}) 8... Nc6 $5 {Playing against the e3-e4 advance.} 9. a3 $1 ({Sensibly keeping Black out of b4. Please don't fall for} 9. e4 $4 Nb4 10. Qb1 fxe4 11. Nxe4 Nxe4 12. Qxe4 e5 {, already with a near-decisive initiative for Black.}) 9... e5 10. h3 $5 {A useful semi-waiting move, if also one which, of course, supports the g2-g4 break. This type of position is largely quite comfortable for Black with White's king on g1, but here White instead wants to house the king on the queenside.} e4 11. Nd2 {White will castle long, the g2-g4 break will begin to undermine e4 and there's always a timely d4-d5 too, as White surely stands slightly better in part too due to Black's slightly congested position.} *

