1. Nf3 h5 $6 {You may also get to face this in blitz, but it's certainly not a move to fear.} 2. c4 ({Our favourite advance works well here, but so, of course, do} 2. d4 {and}) (2. e4 {.}) 2... h4 3. h3 $1 {The simplest course, fixing the pawn on h4.} e6 4. e3 {Another of our favourite early pawn moves. White may complete development with Nc3, d2-d4 and Bd3 or simply stick with a b2-b3 and Bb2 approach. Black can try to be hyper aggressive, but it won't get them very far.} f5 5. b3 {As so often, the bishop will be pretty well placed on the long diagonal for a Classical or Stonewall Dutch style scenario.} Nf6 6. Bb2 Be7 7. Nc3 {Clearly it won't be at all easy for Black to force through ...g5-g4, meaning that White can calmly complete development with Be2 and O-O, after which we may well look to head forwards, be it with Ne5 or Ng5 and f2-f4.} *

