1. Nf3 h6 {Hinting at a reversed Grob (or Borg) style set-up with ...g5.} (1... e5 $2 2. Nxe5 {There goes a clear pawn, and in a position where White will be able to get in at least one of d2-d4 and e2-e4.} Nc6 3. d4 $5 {Refusing to back down so and retreat the knight until attacked by a pawn is generally a good approach in such positions. White may now follow up with some combination of Bf4, Nc3 and e2-e4.} Nxe5 4. dxe5 d6 {This was Demidov-Shirazi, Internet (blitz) 2021, where Black's compensation was virtually non-existent. After} 5. Bf4 {White is simply a clear pawn up and may even meet} g5 $5 {with the super cool} 6. Bc1 {.}) (1... g5 $2 2. Nxg5 {The knight will drop back to f3 if attacked, once again both d2-d4 and e2-e4 are imminent, and Black must even watch out that they don't run into an awkward attack on f7 after Qh5.} e5 3. d4 $1 {Challenging in the centre without delay.} h6 4. Nf3 e4 5. Ng1 $5 {Undeveloping, but the knight is bound for e2 and Black's kingside hardly a pretty sight (5.Nfd2 is also somewhat better for White).} d5 {In Chigaev-Beerdsen, Internet (blitz) 2021, White was now content with} 6. e3 {and a pawn-up version of a French. It's also possible to aim for even more with 6.Bf4 White is a clear pawn up, with e2-e3 set to follow and then the c2-c4 break.}) 2. c4 g5 3. Nc3 $5 {Again, we develop the knights before the central pawns, aiming especially here to lure Black forwards on the kingside.} g4 $6 4. Nh4 $1 {The knight gazes at a potentially fine spot on f5 and is actually quite safe here, since g2-g3 is imminent.} e6 5. g3 Be7 6. d4 $5 ({Here} 6. Ng2 {followed by d2-d4 definitely favours White, but we'd be extremely tempted to offer a pawn so to fight for the initiative. Either h2-h3 or e2-e4 will follow if Black doesn't accept the gambit.}) 6... Bxh4 7. gxh4 Qxh4 8. Bf4 {A superb square for the bishop and White may well be able to increase the pressure down the h2-b8 diagonal with c4-c5 and/ or Nb5. Meanwhile h2-h3 will be quick to bring the rook on h1 into play and the engines certainly agree about White's compensation, Stockfish already assessing the position as almost '+2.5'.} *

