or the calm 6.h3 when 6...cxd4 7.Nxd4 would be a case of hello, Maroczy Bind!}) 5... g4 6. Ng1 $1 ({A calm retreat, avoiding the mess of} 6. Nh4 e5 {.}) 6... h5 7. Be3 {Developing while reinforcing the centre. White may even now be able to go Qd2 and O-O-O, as well as begin to fight back on the kingside with h2-h3.} Nc6 8. h3 $5 f5 $6 ({Preparing to open lines, whether straight away or after} 8... e5 9. d5 Nd4 {.}) 9. hxg4 hxg4 10. Rxh8 {Clearly one of the main points behind White's last two moves as he begins to play to exploit Black's potentially overextended kingside.} Bxh8 11. Nge2 $1 ({Here exchanging on f5 was far from bad in Melkumyan-Carlsen, Titled Tuesday Blitz 2022, where the cheeky} 11. Nh3 $5 {must also have been tempting.}) *

