1. Nf3 Nc6 2. d4 ({Black gets ready to meet our favourite} 2. c4 {with} e5 {and a reversed Sicilian.}) {Just like against 1...d6, this is a good response, cutting out ...e5 in its entirety while threatening to push on to d5.} 2... d5 {Invariably played to compete for the centre.} 3. c4 ({Accepting the transposition to a Chigorin Defence where White has decent prospects of emerging with an edge. If you might prefer something independent, both the London style} 3. Bf4 {and Colle-esque}) (3. e3 $5 {are decent alternatives.}) 3... Bg4 {Black's main move by some margin, getting the bishop outside the pawn chain before going ...e6, if clearly not forced.} 4. Nc3 {Increasing the pressure against d5, an important square in the upcoming struggle.} e6 5. cxd5 exd5 ({Forcing the pace. Now} 5... Bxf3 6. exf3 exd5 7. Bb5 $1 {would once again be very pleasant for White.}) 6. Qb3 $5 ({This move lags some way behind} 6. Bf4 {in the popularity stakes, but increasing the pressure against d5 and b7 is certainly thematic with Black's bishop away from c8. White is also setting a little trap.}) 6... Bxf3 {Black's most logical continuation, looking to counter against d4.} 7. exf3 $1 {The right way to recapture as we dangle d4 before Black.} Qe7+ $1 8. Be3 Qb4 $5 ({The most natural way to block the open file. Now} 8... Nxd4 $2 9. Qxb7 Rd8 10. O-O-O {might well lead to a quick win for White.}) 9. Qc2 $5 {Keeping queens on and so intending Qd2, as well as a2-a3.} Nxd4 10. Qd2 Ne6 ({As} 10... c5 $2 11. a3 {wouldn't be at all advisable for Black, White will regain the pawn on d5, with definite chances for an edge.}) 11. a3 {Played so that Qxd5 will come with tempo and offer a queen exchange.} Qb3 ({Note that} 11... Qa5 12. Qxd5 Qxd5 13. Nxd5 {will lead to the same thing.}) 12. Qxd5 Qxd5 13. Nxd5 {We can certainly say that White's development is free and easy, with Bc4 and O-O-O imminent.} O-O-O 14. O-O-O Z0 ({Perhaps the doubled pawns mean that Black is OK, but we'd be happier as White with the two bishops. Bc4 will come next, unless Black goes} 14... c6 15. Nc3 {, thereby generating some pressure down the a2-g8 diagonal and Black must also watch out that a7 doesn't simply drop off (due to ...b6; Ba6+).}) *

