1. Nf3 Nc6 2. d4 ({Black gets ready to meet our favourite} 2. c4 {with} e5 {and a reversed Sicilian.}) {Just like against 1...d6, this is a good response, cutting out ...e5 in its entirety while threatening to push on to d5.} 2... d5 {Invariably played to compete for the centre.} 3. c4 ({Accepting the transposition to a Chigorin Defence where White has decent prospects of emerging with an edge. If you might prefer something independent, both the London style} 3. Bf4 {and Colle-esque}) (3. e3 $5 {are decent alternatives.}) 3... Bg4 {Black's main move by some margin, getting the bishop outside the pawn chain before going ...e6, if clearly not forced.} 4. Nc3 {Increasing the pressure against d5, an important square in the upcoming struggle.} e6 5. cxd5 exd5 ({Forcing the pace. Now} 5... Bxf3 6. exf3 exd5 7. Bb5 $1 {would once again be very pleasant for White.}) 6. Qb3 $5 ({This move lags some way behind} 6. Bf4 {in the popularity stakes, but increasing the pressure against d5 and b7 is certainly thematic with Black's bishop away from c8. White is also setting a little trap.}) 6... Bxf3 {Black's most logical continuation, looking to counter against d4.} 7. exf3 $1 {The right way to recapture as we dangle d4 before Black.} Qe7+ $1 8. Be3 O-O-O ({The most natural way to block the open file. Now} 8... Nxd4 $2 9. Qxb7 Rd8 10. O-O-O {might well lead to a quick win for White.}) 9. Rc1 $1 (9. O-O-O {has been preferred in the correspondence world, but this looks like another good idea from Axel Smith, who relays in 'e3 Poison' that it brought him a victory in the 2009 Rolf Martens Memorial (rapid). Now Nxd5 is definitely a threat.}) ({Note that after} 9. Rc1 {,} Nxd4 $2 10. Qa4 Nc6 11. Ba6 $1 {wouldn’t be too wise for Black.}) 9... Qb4 10. Qxb4 ({The simple choice, although the engines prefer} 10. Qd1 $5 {.}) 10... Bxb4 11. Bd3 {White has a pleasant edge with the two bishops. Clearly we might expand on the queenside with a2-a3 and b2-b4, with h2-h4-h5 another way of annexing some useful space on the other flank. The king can head to g1 or just sit on d2.} *

